HB 900 Original 2026 Regular Session Braud
Abstract: Requires the dept. to establish a fund to be utilized for repairing damaged state
property with funds from a traffic accident recovered by the Dept. of Transportation
and Development.
Proposed law requires the Dept. of Transportation and Development to establish a fund for
the collection of funds recovered by the dept. for damage caused to state property by traffic
accidents.
Proposed law requires that the funds collected be utilized to repair the damaged state
property or to reimburse the district or local governing authority that paid for the repairs to
state property.
Proposed law excludes any costs expended by the dept. to recover the funds from the party
responsible for causing the damage to state property.
(Adds R.S. 48:2251 and 2252)
